    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>use <a href=\"https://github.com/alexruiz/fest-assert-2.x/wiki/One-minute-starting-guide\" rel=\"noreferrer\">fest assert 2.0</a> whenever possible EDIT: <a href=\"http://joel-costigliola.github.io/assertj/assertj-core.html\" rel=\"noreferrer\">assertj</a> may have more assertions (a fork)</p>\n\n<pre><code>assertThat(x).contains(\"foo\");\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 199370,
      "reputation" : 20269,
      "user_id" : 444639,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 84,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/76bfe9645715492707b67ed7d04bc73a?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "Rylander",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/444639/rylander"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 11,
    "last_activity_date" : 1377729226,
    "last_edit_date" : 1495542852,
    "creation_date" : 1377729226,
    "answer_id" : 18499388,
    "question_id" : 1092219,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Use hamcrest Matcher <code>containsString()</code></p>\n\n<pre><code>// Hamcrest assertion\nassertThat(person.getName(), containsString(\"myName\"));\n\n// Error Message\njava.lang.AssertionError:\nExpected: a string containing \"myName\"\n     got: \"some other name\"\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>You can optional add an even more detail error message.</p>\n\n<pre><code>// Hamcrest assertion with custom error message\nassertThat(\"my error message\", person.getName(), containsString(\"myName\"));\n\n// Error Message\njava.lang.AssertionError: my error message\nExpected: a string containing \"myName\"\n     got: \"some other name\"\n</code></pre>\n\n<p><em>Posted my answer to a duplicate question <a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/15711180/assertion-fail-message-for-string-contains-substring/15711242\">here</a></em></p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 5261579,
      "reputation" : 21,
      "user_id" : 4202979,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/970ee405e4a40fad2e1006430a1a8197?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
      "display_name" : "LEON DENIS",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/4202979/leon-denis"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 2,
    "last_activity_date" : 1463147591,
    "creation_date" : 1463147591,
    "answer_id" : 37211834,
    "question_id" : 1092219,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Another variant is</p>\n\n<pre><code>Assert.assertThat(actual, new Matches(expectedRegex));\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Moreover in <code>org.mockito.internal.matchers</code> there are some other interesting matchers, like <code>StartWith</code>, <code>Contains</code> etc.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 3145697,
      "reputation" : 1653,
      "user_id" : 2660216,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 33,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/bfbc9819fa7d2e93e735f7edd813f0f8?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "P Kuijpers",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/2660216/p-kuijpers"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1554399488,
    "last_edit_date" : 1554399488,
    "creation_date" : 1479564022,
    "answer_id" : 40693748,
    "question_id" : 1092219,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>I've tried out many answers on this page, none really worked:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li><em>org.hamcrest.CoreMatchers.containsString</em> does not compile, cannot resolve method.</li>\n<li><em>JUnitMatchers.containsString</em> is depricated (and refers to <em>CoreMatchers.containsString</em>).</li>\n<li><em>org.hamcrest.Matchers.containsString</em>: NoSuchMethodError</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>So instead of writing readable code, I decided to use the simple and workable approach mentioned in the question instead.</p>\n\n<p>Hopefully another solution will come up. </p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 3913115,
      "reputation" : 1101,
      "user_id" : 3237814,
      "user_type" : "registered",
